      "title": "<span id=\"#15487\" class=\"scroll-m-16 text-3xl font-bold flex items-center\"><h1 class=\"inline !mb-1 scroll-m-16 text-3xl font-bold\">appall</h1><div class=\"pl-2 flex-1 text-textSecondary text-xl font-serif\">(v.)</div></span>",
      "html": "<p>也有 <span class=\"foreign notranslate\">appal</span>，早在14世纪，意为“褪色”； 约在1400年，意为“变得苍白”，源自古法语 <span class=\"foreign notranslate\">apalir</span> “变得或使变得苍白”，由 <span class=\"foreign notranslate\">a-</span> “向”（见 <a href=\"/cn/word/ad-\" title=\"Etymology, meaning and definition of ad- \" class=\"crossreference notranslate\">ad-</a>)和 <span class=\"foreign notranslate\">palir</span> “变得苍白”组成，源自拉丁语 <span class=\"foreign notranslate\">pallere</span> “变得苍白”（源自 PIE 词根 <a href=\"/cn/word/*pel-\" title=\"Etymology, meaning and definition of *pel- \" rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"crossreference notranslate\">*pel-</a>（1）“苍白”）。及物动词意为“使惊愕或震惊”，始见于1530年代。相关词汇： <a href=\"/cn/word/appalled\" title=\"Etymology, meaning and definition of Appalled \" class=\"crossreference notranslate\">Appalled</a>； <a href=\"/cn/word/appalling\" title=\"Etymology, meaning and definition of appalling \" class=\"crossreference notranslate\">appalling</a>。</p><ins class=\"adsbygoogle relative inline-block transition-all inline-block h-[250px] w-[300px]\" data-ad-slot=\"4000736339\" data-adtest=\"off\" data-ad-format=\"auto\" data-full-width-responsive=\"true\"></ins>"
    }
  ],
